{"t":"2026-05-30T03:14:06.279Z","event":"chronicle.append","detail":{"op":"chronicle.append","buffered":1,"entry":{"t":"2026-05-30T03:14:06.275Z","text":"Session 1: Aldric Thorne, lone survivor of a Vellmark convoy, woke at Greywater Crossing with no memory of the final hour. Met Maren the ferryman keeper. Tracked woodcutter Osric into the Ashwood at night, killed a silver-eyed thrall wolf, rescued Osric and learned of a clearing with a breathing stone that wasn't there last year. Spoke with Ashwarden Eska: 41 boundary stones seal something old in the Ashwood; one was removed by Vellmark three months ago; a well-dressed Vellmark man asked about moving stones two weeks prior. Attempted memory recovery with hedge doctor Wendel — fumbled, threshold now keyed to Aldric but caught a flash: convoy walked through willingly, blank-faced; a robed figure operating the threshold deliberately. Vellmark guard tokens contain boundary-stone warding in the alloy — someone inside Vellmark knows. Warding disc made into locket. Wendel recommends hunter Sera as companion — her brother was taken six weeks ago. Session paused in Crale, one day before Vellmark factor Corvin arrives."}}}
{"t":"2026-05-30T03:14:07.463Z","event":"chronicle.commit","detail":{"op":"chronicle.commit","entry":{"t":"2026-05-30T03:14:07.458Z","summary":"Session 1 complete: convoy mystery established, threshold identified as directed operation, three leads open (Sera, Corvin, the clearing)"},"clearedFromBuffer":1,"totalEntries":1}}
